                    </row>
					<row>
                        <entry>10</entry>
                        <entry>Audio cables to student PC sound interface (optional)</entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody> 
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    <p>Student modules are connected to the audio hub via an 8-wire flat cable (6) with 8P8C (a.k.a. RJ45) connectors on both ends (<xref keyref="install_equipment/cabels_png" type="fig"/>&#160;).</p>
    <p>The 8-wire flat cable is installed between the audio hub and each of the student modules. The cable is terminated by 8P8C connectors that are crimped on by a suitable crimping tool (not included).</p>
    <note type="important">The connector cable is wired in "straight through" mode (known as T568), i.e. pins 1 through 8 on one end are connected to pins 1 through 8 on the other end.</note>
    <fig id="cabels_png">
        <title>Connector cable</title>
        <image href="img/cabels.png" placement="break">
            <alt>Connector cable</alt>
        </image>
    </fig>
    <p>After connecting the cables and replacing the cover, the student module can be permanently mounted on the student desk.</p>
  </conbody>
